body:
@atlimit8: Chrono Legionnaire should not use this at all. Chrono Legionnaire should have two armaments, with one only used for upgrading the target's TargetType from casual to Temporal only along with DisableUpgrade recoloring the target to light white, a WithDecoration giving the temporal sparkles and the another one only affecting Temporal TargetType'd targets, maintaining this upgrade and delivering the damage entirely. It has no relation to this atm.... the Paratroopers refactor is more related due to the current TargetType-upgrade proposal disallowing to have different TargetType setup for paratroopers and for temporal weapons (and for RA2 IronCurtain because in RA2, AI units didn't even wasted shots for Ironcurtained units, something OpenRA does).

Both the TeslaBoost and GivesTeslaBoost trait can be replaced via an upgradable Armament on the coil with a weapon having GrantUpgrade warheads to get it upgraded on SHOK's side, with both of SHOK's armaments sharing the AmmoPool to prevent SHOK charging both the coil and attacking at the same time. This needs no change in the code at GrantUpgrade, only YAML level modding - Armaments needs a change just because of #8444 alone.

The sole thing which shall stay from the current state of this PR is the Upgradable implementation of RequiresPower. Everything else can be axed and if @matija-hustic does not have time, I gladly fill a PR against his PR tomorrow to do this YAML modding.
